        <h1>Table Tennis</h1>
        <p><code>Table Tennis</code> (also known as ping-pong) is a racket sport derived from <code>tennis</code> but distinguished by its playing surface
        being atop a stationary table, rather than the court on which players stand. Either individually or in teams of two,
        players take alternating turns returning a light, hollow ball over the table's net onto the opposing half of the court
        using small rackets until they fail to do so, which results in a point for the opponent. <code>Play is fast, requiring quick
        reaction and constant attention</code>, and is characterized by an emphasis on spin, which can affect the ball's trajectory
        more than in other ball sports.</p>
